Not sure if it is the same bug. But I have a board that includes two projects. The board column configuration page missed all status from one particular workflow of one of the projects. After identifying and removing the part of the query that caused the problem, all status appeared. I moved that part of the filter query to a subfilter and everything works as intended.

Original query:
{code:java}
project = "Project A" AND issuetype in standardIssueTypes() AND Sprint in openSprints() AND Sprint not in futureSprints()) OR (project = "Project B" AND (status not in (StatusA, StatusB) OR status in (StatusA, StatusB) AND updated > -1d)) ORDER BY Rank ASC{code}
Problematic part that I moved to a subfilter
{code:java}
status not in (StatusA, StatusB) OR status in (StatusA, StatusB) AND updated > -1d{code}

Paulo - I've been frustrated by this issue as well... but saw on another thread (which I can't find the link) that the best workaround is to do the following;
# Create your query w/ the exact parameters you want, but add a single quotation mark at the beginning of the query name ("QueryName). By doing that ("QueryName) your query will come up as one of the first items on the search. # Go to the board configuration ('General and filter') page & try to find your query in the 'Saved Filter' section (it should be right at the top). # Once you've found it, select it and leverage it for your board. # Then go back to your issue queue ("QueryName) and remove the " at the beginning of your query name (since you were able to find it - and it's no longer required :) ).
Hope the steps above helps... I know I'll be leveraging it for a while (until Atlassian fixes the issue).

