h3. Issue Summary
For multi-cascade fields the cascadeOption("Parent","child") works fine, the the ("Parent",none) also works fine. Except when you combine both.
The JQL won't work even if the search is combined with other JQL search clause.
Also, this bug is impacting customers if the filter gadget is used with grouping by the Cascading field.
h3. Steps to Reproduce # Create a Multi-Cascade Field. # Search using the next JQL that works fine {code:java} "CascadeField[Select List (cascading)]" in cascadeOption("Option1","Option1A")) {code}
# Search using the next JQL that works fine {code:java} "CascadeField[Select List (cascading)]" in cascadeOption("Option1",none)) {code}
# Combine both JQLs, it fails {code:java} "CascadeField[Select List (cascading)]" in cascadeOption("Option1",none)) OR "CascadeField[Select List (cascading)]" in cascadeOption("Option1","Option1A")) {code}
# Combine with usual JQL search clause {code} "CascadeField[Select List (cascading)]" in cascadeOption("Option1",none) and project = ABC {code}
h3. Expected Results
JQL should return the combination of the individual results h3. Actual Results
the CascadeOption("Option1",none) breaks the results. h3. Workaround
No workaround.

