item.description:
h2. Steps to reproduce
 * Set up Confluence 6.6.7 with a SQL Server 2014 v12.0.5589 database (may affect other versions of SQL Server as well)
 * Populate the database with data with dimensions similar to this:
 ** Over 2 million rows in the content table
 ** At least one user with ~10,000 documents or versions of documents modified
 * Visit the recently worked on tab in the dashboard

h2. Expected results

Dashboard tab loads in a timely manner.
h2. Actual results

Dashboard tab never loads. The database CPU spikes for a long time and the query takes about 30 minutes to return. Due to the database being so busy this can cause stability issues causing the rest of Confluence to stop working as well.
h2. Workaround

The best workaround at the moment is to disable the feature. This involves 2 steps:
 # Modify your reverse proxy settings to block requests to the search endpoint when the any requests matching this pattern is issued:
{noformat}
/rest/api/content/search\?.*recentlyModifiedPagesAndBlogPostsByUser.*{noformat}
Unfortunately there is no way to do this within Tomcat or Confluence itself.
 # Add the following CSS to remove the link from the dashboard:
{code:java}
.confluence-dashboard li.nav-item-container-recently-worked {
    display: none;
}
{code}

Some entries in the Audit Log are not consistent when the action is not performed by a specific user.
h3. Steps to reproduce:
 # Create a User Directory and set it "Read Only, with Local Groups";
 # Define some groups in Default Group Memberships;
 # Save and sync the directory;
 # Log into Confluence with a User to be added to the default groups;
 # Check the Audit Log;

h3. Expected results

We see a change "User added to group" made by the user "System", just as any other automatic user change, like a directory sync.
h3. Actual results

The user responsible for the change is "Anonymous". There are also the IP addresses from Confluence host server and from the client machine used to log in.

*Notes*
If the group doesn't exist when the action above is triggered, we can also see an entry "Group created" changed by the last user that edited the User Directory along with the same IP addresses described above.

