h3. Issue Summary

Cannot create a repo via /2.0/repositories/\{workspace}/\{repo_slug} with project access token (PAT)
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # create a PAT from project settings with scope repository:admin
 # try creating a repository using [create repository API endpoint|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/bitbucket/rest/api-group-repositories/#api-repositories-workspace-repo-slug-post]

h3. Expected Results

The repository should be created
h3. Actual Results

The below error is thrown in the API response:
{noformat}
{
	"type": "error",
	"error": {
		"message": "You do not have access to view this workspace."
	}
}
{noformat}
h3. Workaround
 * Use an [App password|https://support.atlassian.com/bitbucket-cloud/docs/app-passwords/] for authentication instead of an access token

Example:
{code:none}
curl --request POST \
--url 'https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/{workspace}/{repo_slug}' \
--user '{username}:{app_apssword}' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data '{
    "is_private": "true",
    "scm": "git",
    "project": {
        "key": "TEST"
        }
    }'
{code}

comments.text:
@Eric Waite According to Atlassian, this is the workaround....
{quote}For now, the best way to deal with creating new repositories within a given workspace is to use workspace access tokens (WAT) instead. This feature is documented here:
{panel}
[https://support.atlassian.com/bitbucket-cloud/docs/using-workspace-access-tokens/]
{panel}
In short, to create one, all you have to do is access the workspace settings (as an admin) and click on access tokens, under "security". You can then follow the on-screen instructions to complete the token creation.

You will need to grant the token access to the account, project, and repository scopes for it to be able to create new repos.
{quote}

