item.description:
h3. Issue Summary
When attempting to use the SSH 2FA method, with the command below:
{code}
ssh git@bitbucket.org recovery_codes
{code}

The following error message is thrown:
{code}
{"type": "error", "error": {"message": "You cannot administer personal accounts of other users."}}
{code}

Or even, the request is successful but the recovery codes are missing in the response:
{code}
Your single-use recovery codes are

Once logged in, you should immediately visit
https://bitbucket.org/account/user/git/two-step-verification/
to add a new two-step device.
Thank you for using Atlassian Bitbucket.
{code}

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Set up an SSH key and 2FA on your account
 # On your terminal, run the following command, as described [here|https://support.atlassian.com/bitbucket-cloud/docs/enable-two-step-verification/]:
{code}
ssh git@bitbucket.org recovery_codes
{code}

h3. Expected Results
The recovery codes are correctly displayed on the terminal.

h3. Actual Results
The following error is thrown:
{code}
{"type": "error", "error": {"message": "You cannot administer personal accounts of other users."}}
{code}
Or the Recovery Codes are missing in the response body;

h3. Workaround

Currently, the only known workaround is to disable your account 2FA using the e-mail method described here, under "Disable two-step verification":
https://support.atlassian.com/bitbucket-cloud/docs/enable-two-step-verification/

h3. Issue Summary
When using a Markdown list without a preceding blank line will render the items on a single line. Note that this is acceptable in traditional Markdown (as per {{Markdown.pl}}), however [in the CommonMark spec, it is noted that lists do not need a preceding blank line|https://spec.commonmark.org/0.29/#example-273].
h3. Steps to Reproduce # Suppose the following code is part of a Markdown formatted file: {code} I need to buy - new shoes - a coat - a plane ticket {code}
h3. Expected Results The code is rendered as follows:
{quote} I need to buy - new shoes - a coat - a plane ticket {quote}
h3. Actual Results
The code is rendered as follows: {quote} I need to buy - new shoes - a coat - a plane ticket {quote}
h3. Workaround
Use the {{Markdown.pl}} style lists which require a blank line before the list.

h3. Issue Summary
 * Responses from the *Pipelines* endpoint returns an invalid URL for both *self* and *steps* fields which can't be accessed with regular *<username:apppassword>* authorization header;
 * 
{code:java}
"links": {
        "self": {
          "href": "https://bitbucket-pipelines.prod.public.atl-paas.net//rest/1.0/accounts/{workspace_uuid}/repositories/{repo_uuid}/pipelines/{build_uuid}"
        },
        "steps": {
          "href": "https://bitbucket-pipelines.prod.public.atl-paas.net//rest/1.0/accounts/{workspace_uuid}/repositories/{repo_uuid}/pipelines/{build_uuid}/steps"
        }
      } {code}

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Make an API call to the *Pipelines* endpoint for any repository
 # In the results, you will see a *Links* object with two URLs: *self* and *steps;*
 # Try to make a GET request to that URL;

h3. Expected Results

Results should use the actual *api.bitbucket.org* domain, making it possible to fetch results from these URLs;
h3. Actual Results

Fetching the build and the steps from these URLs fail with authorization error:
{code:java}
{
  "error": {
    "message": "Unauthorized",
    "detail": "No authorization provider header specified.",
    "data": {
      "key": "rest-service.rest-service.unauthorized",
      "arguments": {}
    }
  }
} {code}
h3. Workaround

Directly fetch the build and steps from our API sub-domain;
{code:java}
/2.0/repositories/{workspace}/{repo_slug}/pipelines/{pipeline_uuid} {code}
and
{code:java}
/2.0/repositories/{workspace}/{repo_slug}/pipelines/{pipeline_uuid}/steps/ {code}

h3. Issue Summary

When querying for repository variables and deployments on a repository wit additional results, you will get a pagination with a next URL to query the remaining results.

However, for repository variables endpoint, it is providing an incorrect URL such as:
{panel}
https://SOME_INVALID_DOMAIN_HERE/rest/1.0/accounts/...
{panel}

OR
{panel}
https://SOME_INVALID_DOMAIN_HERE/rest/2.0/accounts/...
{panel}

Although the URL endpoint is clearly incorrect, using it throws the following error:
 {
 "error": {
 "data": {
 "arguments": {},
 "key": "rest-service.rest-service.unauthorized"
 },
 "detail": "No authorization provider header specified.",
 "message": "Unauthorized"
 }
 }
h3. Steps to Reproduce
Repository variables:
 # Create more than 10 repository variables on a repository
 # Run the GET API for /pipelines_config/variables/
 # Check the "Next" URL given by the above API

Deployments
# Create multiple deployments in a repository 
# User the GET method on the {{/2.0/repositories/workspace/repos_slug/deployments/}} endpoint
# Check the "Next" URL given by the above API


h3. Expected Results
The next URL would be given for the /pipelines_config/variables/ or /deployments/ endpoints.

h3. Actual Results
The next URL is given for {{/rest/1.0/accounts/}} or {{/rest/2.0/accounts/}} endpoints.

h3. Workaround

The workaround is to add a larger pagelen to get the results without the use of the "Next" URL.
 Example:
{code:java}
curl -X GET -u $USERNAME:$APP_PASSWORD "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/$WORKSPACE_ID/$REPO__SLUG/pipelines_config/variables/?pagelen=100"
{code}

h3. Issue Summary
As per the title, if you attempt to run a Pipelines build manually, you will see the following error message, in case you are using Safari:
{code}
An unidentified error occurred. Please try again.
{code}

The build will execute just fine, but the error will always show up.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Log in to Bitbucket using Safari;
 # Navigate to any repository that has a valid bitbucket-pipelines.yml configuration in it;
 # Click on the Pipelines tab > Run Pipelines;
 # Run any Pipelines build;
 # You will see the following error message
{code}
An unidentified error occurred. Please try again.
{code}

h3. Expected Results
The Pipelines build will execute normally, without any error messages showing up in the UI

h3. Actual Results
The below exception is thrown:
{noformat}
An unidentified error occurred. Please try again.
{noformat}

h3. Workaround

Use either Chrome or Firefox, which don't have this error message, or ignore the error message altogether.

