item.description:
{code} pipelines: pull-requests: &#39;**&#39;: {code}
returns
!3176947538-image.png|thumbnail!\\ ‌
instead full form like within branch driven pipeline
{code} pipelines: default: {code}
!831595848-image.png|thumbnail!
h3. Expected: Always return full form.
h3. Workaround
Add the following command in your script, prior to using the BITBUCKET_COMMIT variable. {code} - export BITBUCKET_COMMIT=$(git log -1 --format="%H" $BITBUCKET_COMMIT 2>/dev/null) - echo $BITBUCKET_COMMIT{code}
BITBUCKET_COMMIT will then return the full hash.

